title: Two teenagers killed when car hits tree in Howden - BBC News
text:
Two teenagers killed when car hits tree in Howden 8 February 2017 Close share panel Two teenagers have died after the car they were travelling in crashed in East Yorkshire. 
Police said the vehicle left the road and hit a tree near Barnhill Lane at Howden at 20:15 GMT on Tuesday. 
Two passengers in the car, a 16-year-old girl from Selby and a 17-year-old boy from Goole, died at the scene. 
The driver of the car, a 19-year-old man, sustained minor injuries and has been arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving.
